  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Description&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Non-functional requirements define qualities&amp;nbsp;or attributes&amp;nbsp;the system must exhibit in order to meet&#xD;
    stakeholders needs,&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;typically describing&amp;nbsp;constraints on the behavior&amp;nbsp;of the system. Non-functional&#xD;
    requirements should be&amp;nbsp;specified as objectively as possible and must be&amp;nbsp;testable.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The IEEE-Std 830 - 1993 includes the following types of non-functional requirements:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Performance&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Reliability&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Maintainability&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Security&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Portability&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Operational&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This solution&amp;nbsp;focuses on performance, reliability or security requirements early in the development lifecycle for&#xD;
    mission-critical or high-availability systems, as well as&amp;nbsp;usability requirements for highly-interactive systems.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Symptoms&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Symptoms that indicate the need to&amp;nbsp;improve non-functional requirements&amp;nbsp;include:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Occurrence of non-functional requirement issues&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        High number of help desk calls&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Resolution time is high for reported incidents&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Solutions&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
